LEGISLATURE OF THE STATE OF IDAHO
Sixty-eighth Legislature First Regular Session - 2025
IN THE HOUSE OF REPRESENTATIVES
HOUSE BILL NO. 13
BY TRANSPORTATION AND DEFENSE COMMITTEE
1 AN ACT
2 RELATING TO RULES OF THE ROAD; AMENDING SECTION 49-666, IDAHO CODE, TO ESTAB-
3 LISH A CERTAIN EXEMPTION REGARDING SAFETY HELMET REQUIREMENTS AND STAN-
4 DARDS AND TO MAKE TECHNICAL CORRECTIONS; AND DECLARING AN EMERGENCY AND
5 PROVIDING AN EFFECTIVE DATE.
6 Be It Enacted by the Legislature of the State of Idaho:
7 SECTION 1. That Section 49-666, Idaho Code, be, and the same is hereby
8 amended to read as follows:
9 49-666. MOTORCYCLE, MOTORBIKE, UTV AND ATV SAFETY HELMETS -- REQUIRE-
10 MENTS AND STANDARDS. No person under eighteen (18) years of age shall ride
11 upon or be permitted to operate a motorcycle, motorbike, utility type vehi-
12 cle or an all-terrain vehicle unless at all times when so operating or rid-
13 ing upon the vehicle he is wearing, as part of his motorcycle, motorbike, UTV
14 or ATV equipment, a protective safety helmet of a type and quality equal to
15 or better than the standards established for helmets by the director, except
16 the. The provisions of this section shall not apply when such vehicles are
17 operated or ridden on private property, or when are used as an implement of
18 husbandry, and. The provisions of this section shall also not apply to com-
19 pletely enclosed autocycles or to UTVs that are equipped with a roll cage and
20 seat belts.
21 SECTION 2. An emergency existing therefor, which emergency is hereby
22 declared to exist, this act shall be in full force and effect on and after
23 July 1, 2025.

